profile_positions.description:
The aim of my research is to facilitate personalized adaptive radiotherapy to improve treatment outcome using Deep Learning. More information on the sub-topics I am focusing on can be found below:

•  Automatic Tumor Segmentation in FDG-PET and CT scans of patients with oropharyngeal cancer: 

    1.)  Development of novel deep learning algorithms for segmentation (HECKTOR Challenge 2021);

    2.)  Identification of these methods' flows when applied to the medical imaging domain;

    3.)  Development of a novel deep learning method that makes available the uncertainty derived from the tumor segmentation task;

    4.)  Investigation of strategies that bridge the existing gap between model deployment and clinical implementation. 

•  Prediction of patient outcomes, namely Local Control, Regional Control, Distant Metastasis-Free Survival and Overall Survival from the FDG-PET/CT images and available clinical data:

   1.)   Investigating the potential of various image modalities as input for predicting patient outcomes;

   2.)   Survival Analysis.

• Gathering, analyzing and understanding data to support stategic and operative business decisions;

• Collaborating with development and marketing teams in order to achieve solutions to meet business goals;

• Daily, weekly, monthly monitoring according to Company's KPIs;

• Proposing and implementing ad hoc analysis in order to reach strategic recommendation in the running business;

• Analyzing marketing campaigns performances from a digital perspective as well as correlated o purchase data;

• Monitoring stock performances, in order to recommends actions for the improvement of the stock’s rotation, working with company buying, CRM and sales functions; 

• Executing statistical models, monitoring and elaborating financial KPI’s reporting directly to CEO and Investors.

• Part of team organizing the second edition of WTT (Wearable Tech Torino), the first Italian event on Wearable Technologies;

• Lead a 5-people team with responsibility for the sale of exhibition space and sponsorship packages for large companies and start-ups;

• Lead a 5-people team responsible for the sale of ICT services, including mobile apps, SEO&SAM, web sites, social media marketing, brand and graphic design.

J.E.To.P. is the Junior Enterprise of the Politecnico di Torino University, it's a no-profit organization that aims to fill the gap between studies and work. 
Founded in 1995 in one of the most prestigious universities of Italy and Europe, J.E.To.P. has always renewed thanks to his proactive members which are students coming from all the fields of engineering and architecture.
